# Frontend Architecture (Core)

- Use feature-based structure. Each feature owns its `components`, `hooks`, `store`, `services`, `types`, and tests.
- Keep `shared` for truly cross-feature code only (base UI, common utils, constants, shared types).
- Do not create uncontrolled cross-feature imports. A feature can import from `shared`, but not directly from other features unless there is an explicit public API.
- Prefer path aliases over deep relative paths:

```ts
// bad
import { Button } from "../../../../../components";

// good
import { Button } from "@/shared/components";
```

- Configure alias in `tsconfig.json`:

```json
"paths": {
  "@/*": ["src/*"]
}
```
